xi$. Moreover, we discuss the specific heat $C_V$ and the\ntemperature dependence of the excitation spectrum. As approaching the\ntransition point $J_2^c$ some unusual features were found, such as negative\nspin-spin correlations at temperatures above $T_C$ even though the ground state\nis ferromagnetic or an increase of the spin stiffness with growing temperature.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 27 May 2015 08:30:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 16 Jul 2015 08:59:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-07-17"}
