 early universe reaching $\\rho_{\\rm acc} \\gtrsim\n10^5M_\\odot{\\rm Mpc^{-3}}$ by $z\\simeq 10$. This growth must stop by $z \\sim 6$\nand be significantly obscured not to overproduce the soft cosmic X-ray\nbackground (CXB) and its observed coherence with the CIB. We therefore find the\nrange of suitable possibilities at high-$z$ to be narrow, but could possibly be\nwidened by including additional physics and evolution at those epochs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 27 May 2015 08:50:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 23 Sep 2015 07:42:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-11-11"}
